<p>A homeowner notices a dead oak leaning toward their roof after a storm. They grab their phone and search "tree removal near me." Google shows 3 companies in the local map pack. The one with 87 reviews and a 4.8 rating gets the call. The other 2 get nothing.</p>
<p>Tree service SEO determines which arborist gets that call. The U.S. tree trimming services industry generates <a href="https://www.ibisworld.com/united-states/industry/tree-trimming-services/6064/">$39.5 billion annually</a> across 175,000 businesses. Most of those businesses rely on yard signs, truck wraps, and referrals. Those channels work. But they do not scale the way Google does.</p>
<p>The problem is clear. Tree service keywords cost $25 to $65 per click on Google Ads. A single "tree removal near me" click in a competitive metro area can cost more than $50. Spending $2,000 per month on paid ads generates 40 to 60 clicks. That same budget invested in organic SEO compounds over time and eventually delivers hundreds of clicks at $0 per click.</p>
<p>We publish 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. Tree services and home services are among our most active verticals. This guide covers everything an arborist or tree service company needs to rank on Google without an agency.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
